By early Wednesday, the death toll from the Columbine High massacre was confirmed at 15, with the two gunmen included.
The sheriff's initial estimate of 25 dead was due to overlapping areas covered by SWAT teams.
Students at Chatfield High School were urged to wear more moderate clothes following the tragedy.
The community around Columbine came together in grief, with residents emphasizing the importance of unity.
Despite the tragedy, efforts were made to return to normalcy, with students preparing to resume classes and the baseball team receiving support to get back on the field.
The aftermath of the shooting sparked a wave of copycat threats nationwide, prompting swift responses from authorities
